    <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm mb-4">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="h4 mb-3">1. AI-assisted workflow: Codex, Claude Code, and human review</h2>
        <p>In this project, AI acts as a technical pair rather than an autopilot. The human sets priorities, reviews diffs, decides what gets published, and remains responsible for quality. AI helps with code edits, refactoring, translation, structural cleanup, and repetitive implementation work.</p>
        <p><strong>Codex</strong> is used as a coding agent for concrete file edits, command execution, and targeted implementation work inside the repository.</p>
        <p><strong>Claude Code</strong> is used as a second AI perspective for drafting alternatives, refining copy, reviewing structure, and helping shape analysis-heavy pages.</p>
        <p class="mb-0">In practical terms, the workflow is simple: request a change, review the proposed diff, run the build and checks, then publish through version control.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm mb-4">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="h4 mb-3">2. Core building blocks</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">These tools form the day-to-day stack behind the site. On top of them, the project uses its own build pipeline, validation scripts, and cache strategy so external data does not make publishing fragile.</p>
        <div class="table-responsive">
          <table class="table table-hover align-middle">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Tool</th>
                <th>Role</th>
                <th>Learn more</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Eleventy (11ty)</strong></td>
                <td>Eleventy is a static site generator that compiles templates, content, and data into deployable HTML pages.</td>
                <td><a href="https://www.11ty.dev/docs/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Docs</a> · <a href="https://www.11ty.dev/docs/tutorials/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Tutorials</a></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Nunjucks + Markdown</strong></td>
                <td>Nunjucks handles page templates and reusable components. Markdown makes writing and maintaining content simple and readable.</td>
                <td><a href="https://mozilla.github.io/nunjucks/templating.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Nunjucks</a> · <a href="https://www.markdownguide.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Markdown</a></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Bootstrap 5 + Bootstrap Icons</strong></td>
                <td>Bootstrap provides responsive layout primitives and UI components; Bootstrap Icons adds a consistent icon system.</td>
                <td><a href="https://getbootstrap.com/docs/5.3/getting-started/introduction/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Bootstrap</a> · <a href="https://icons.getbootstrap.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Icons</a></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Pagefind</strong></td>
                <td>Pagefind adds fast client-side search to static websites without requiring a separate backend service.</td>
                <td><a href="https://pagefind.app/docs/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Pagefind docs</a></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>GitHub</strong></td>
                <td>GitHub is the source-of-truth for version control, commit history, collaboration, and release workflows.</td>
                <td><a href="https://docs.github.com/en/get-started" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub getting started</a> · <a href="/en/site-changes/">Site changes</a></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>GitHub Actions + GitHub Pages</strong></td>
                <td>Build, SEO checks, search indexing, deployment, and production smoke tests are automated in CI/CD.</td>
                <td><a href="https://docs.github.com/en/actions" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Actions</a> · <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/pages" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Pages</a></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Playwright + custom validation scripts</strong></td>
                <td>Accessibility, navigation, i18n/SEO structure, and overall build health are checked with browser tests and Node-based scripts.</td>
                <td><a href="https://playwright.dev/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Playwright</a> · <a href="/en/site-changes/">Change log</a></td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p class="mb-2">In practice, the pipeline does more than run `11ty` once. Before each build it syncs curated fallback stubs, cleans OG-image output, and generates the site. After that it runs i18n and SEO checks, builds the Pagefind search index, and deploys the result to GitHub Pages.</p>
        <p class="mb-0">Production also includes smoke tests and a scheduled weekly rebuild so the site can refresh itself even when external sources change without a manual content commit.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

